  "---\tWe will do a better job providing you with timely information about issues affecting Enron.  In addition to our existing communication efforts, like e-mail messages and internal publications eBiz and Enron Business, we will post a Q\u0026A on current issues on the Enron intranet at home.enron.com \u003chttp": "//home.enron.com\u003e.  This will give us a consistent message across the organization and will equip you with information when talking to your customers.",
  "1.\tPeople (the high quality of people at Enron was the most widely-cited aspect)": "",
  "2.\tCulture and reputation": "",
  "3.\tWork environment": "",

  "From": "40enron@enron.com",
  "I.  We asked you to identify the top five issues facing Enron today.  The responses were": "",

  "Mime-Version": "1.0",
  "Subject": "Lay It On the Line Survey Results",
  "Therefore, we will make the following changes to the PRC process prior to year-end": "",
  "We all recognize that our external reputation has suffered this year.  The single most important factor that influences our reputation is our actions - how we act and how we communicate those actions as a company and as individual employees.  We recognize that as Enron's ambassador's in the marketplace, the more you know about our strategy, performance and challenges, the more you can help disseminate accurate information about our company.  To ensure you are better informed": "",
  "We also want to make sure that employees know what we are doing going forward": "",
  "We are all concerned about our stock price, which has declined significantly this year.  The primary reasons for the sharp decline from our highs earlier this year include": "",

  "Gramatica injured his hamstring in the fourth quarter on Sunday. The Buccaneers may sign a free agent kicker to replace him in Week 16.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football291.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=pro-player-updates\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=3473\u0026start=30\u0026\"\u003eMore Updates\u003c/A\u003e\u003cTABLE WIDTH=100% BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=1 CELLSPACING=0 BGCOLOR=\"#000099\"\u003e\u003cTR\u003e\u003cTD ALIGN=left\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=arial color=ffffff SIZE=\u003e\u003cB\u003eTeams,\u0026nbsp;Player News\u0026nbsp;\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/TD\u003e\u003c/TR\u003e\u003c/TABLE\u003e\u003c!-- Pizzahut Presenting Logo Spotlight tag - Do not remove until 12-31-01 --\u003e",
  "Gramatica sat out practice Wednesday, but is expected to test his injured leg on Thursday. Doug Brien and Brad Daluiso worked out Wednesday for the Buccaneers, who might sign one if Martin Gramatica can't kick against the Baltimore Ravens this week. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football291.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=3473\u0026key=12429\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eMatt Hasselbeck\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB SEA - Texas Terminators \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/26/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eTrent Dilfer will start this week in place of Hasselbeck, whose separated left shoulder is too sore for him to play.    Coach Mike Holmgren said Wednesday that Hasselbeck aggravated the injury, which he's had since the third week of the season, against the New York Giants last Sunday.   \"There's a chance I might have him and he could play in an emergency-type situation, but he's pretty sore,\" Holmgren said.  \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",

  "From": "noreply@ccomad3.uu.commissioner.com",
  "Gadsden has been practicing this week and may be able to play. But his hamstring injury may limit his productivity. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football291.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=3044\u0026key=1069\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eSteve McNair\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB TEN - Houston Big Ballers \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/28/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eMcNair was limited in practice on Thursday. He is still expected to play this week, but he is a risky Fantasy starter because he will be less than 100 percent healthy. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football291.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=3044\u0026key=1236\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eJimmy Smith\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR JAC - Team Dick \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/28/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eSmith (flu) has missed practice time this week. He is still expected to play. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",
  "McNair was excused from practice on Friday due to a family illness. He is listed as questionable for Sunday's game against Cleveland, but he's expected to start. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football291.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=3044\u0026key=188491\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eLarry Foster\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR DET - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/29/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eFoster (thigh) is expected to play in Sunday's game against Chicago. However, he is far too risky to start at this point in the Fantasy season. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football291.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=3044\u0026key=1186\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eBert Emanuel\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR DET - Blue Balls \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/29/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e",
  "Message-ID": "\u003c24264576.1075855442953.JavaMail.evans@thyme\u003e",
  "Mime-Version": "1.0",
  "Save $.05 a gallon on the gas that keeps your car's engine clean. \u003ca href=\"http": "//www.sportsline.com/links/6/1/226/sffer1228c.cgi\"\u003eClick here\u003c/a\u003e to apply online.\u003cBR\u003e",
  "Subject": "Commissioner.COM E-Reports for Get Bad with Yourself 12/30/01",
  "To": "tstaab@enron.com",
  "Updated 12/28/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eBrookins has returned to practice and is listed as probable. But he still may not see any game action until Week 17.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football291.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=3044\u0026key=1094\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eEmmitt Smith\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB DAL - Team Dick \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/28/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eMicahel Wiley may miss this week's game with a hip injury.   "Updated 12/28/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eFinneran is listed as probable with a knee injury. He is expected to play this week. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football291.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=3044\u0026key=1499\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTyrone Davis\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, TE GB - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/28/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eDavis has been elevated to the No. 2 tight end slot over rookie David Martin. He will see a considerable amount of playing time now that he is healthy, because Green Bay employs many double tight end sets in the red zone. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football291.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=3044\u0026key=1612\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eOronde Gadsden\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR MIA - Team Dick \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/28/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e",
  "Updated 12/30/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eWalls (knee) has been declared inactive for Sunday's game. Kris Mangum will start in his place. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football291.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=3044\u0026key=1871\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTodd Bouman\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB MIN - Grid Iron Goons \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/30/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eBouman has been deactivated for Sunday's game. Spergon Wynn will start in his place. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football291.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=3044\u0026key=187682\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eDez White\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR CHI - President Taft \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/30/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eWhite has been declared inactive for Sunday's game. David Terrell is expected to start in his place. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",
  "Wynn will start Sunday's game against the Green Bay Packers in place of the injured Todd Bouman. Wynn, who played in most of last week's loss to Jacksonville, is far too inexperienced to start this deep into the Fantasy season. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football291.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=3044\u0026key=1041\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eDrew Bledsoe\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB NE - Blue Balls \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/29/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eAccording to published reports, the Chicago Bears are interested in acquiring Bledsoe. With Tom Brady seemingly entrenched as New England's quarterback, it seems that Bledsoe has become expendable to the Patriots.   "Garcia (ribs) has been downgraded to questionable, but he still expects to play this week.   ", WR TEN - C-Dawg's Boyz \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/19/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eMason missed Tuesday's practice with a hip flexor injury. He is not expected to play this week. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",
  ". \"We're going to play Skip more,\" Fisher said. \"We're going to play Skip, if at all possible, as much as he played [Sunday] night ? But I also want to get Eddie [George] 1,000 yards.'' This development will limit George's production over the final three weeks, making him a risky start.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football291.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=782\u0026key=1069\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eSteve McNair\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB TEN - Houston Big Ballers \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/18/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eMcNair will miss Tuesday's practice due to tightness in his lower back which hampered him during Sunday's game against Green Bay. The injury is unrelated to his 1999 surgery to repair a disc in his lower back, and he should return to practice on Wednesday. Provided McNair heals over the next couple of days, he's a safe start for Week 15.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",
  "\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football291.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=782\u0026key=12375\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eDoug Flutie\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB SD - President Taft \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/18/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eChargers Head Coach Mike Riley said Monday that he plans to start Flutie Sunday against Kansas City instead of rookie Drew Brees. While Brees is not expected to play, he may see some playing time in the Week 16 finale against Seattle. Flutie is a very risky player during the Fantasy playoffs, especially in light of the possibility he could sit in favor of Brees at any time.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football291.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=782\u0026key=1645\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003ePriest Holmes\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB KC - Houston Big Ballers \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/18/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e",

  "\u003cBASE HREF=\"http": "//football291.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/\"\u003e",
  "\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=4\u003eLatest NFL Player News\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football291.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=782\u0026key=1177\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTerry Allen\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB BAL - Texas Terminators \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eAllen is ready to assume a larger workload, says the \u003ci\u003eBaltimore Sun\u003c/i\u003e. He may start against the Bengals this week. \"I expect to see more time but I'm still not 100 percent,\" Allen said. \"My hand is going to bother me but I need to be out there on the field to help this team.\"\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football291.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=782\u0026key=1035\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eElvis Grbac\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB BAL - Blue Balls \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e",
  "\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=4\u003eTeam Chick Player News\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football291.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=/mp/player-news\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=782\u0026key=1471\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTony Richardson\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, Reserve RB\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003e Updated 12/19/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",
  "\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eGramatica (knee) was placed on injured reserve. Rookie Cedric Oglesby will be Arizona's placekicker for the final three games of the season. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football291.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=782\u0026key=133462\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eAmos Zereoue\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB PIT - Texas Terminators \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/19/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eZereoue is listed as questionable this week because of a sore shoulder.  He might start at RB if healthy. He replaced Chris Fuamatu-Ma?afala and gained 73 yards Sunday.  \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football291.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=782\u0026key=1152\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eJerome Bettis\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB PIT - Blue Balls \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/19/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e",
  "\u003cIMG SRC=\"http": "//ad.doubleclick.net/ad/N1549.sportsline.com/B44933.5;sz=1x1;ord=1?\" WIDTH=1 HEIGHT=1 BORDER=0\u003e",
  "\u003cIMG WIDTH=1px HEIGHT=1px SRC=\"http": "//football291.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/open_gif?splnid=0631643c5a9e2a58e2d183ed4ff9fc7c\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026email=3f1a7893c3703d39dbb37c2df5d62c48\u0026sport=football\u0026vend=CBS%20SportsLine.com\u0026product=mgmt\u0026time=20011220\u0026type=ereport\u0026random=782\"\u003e\u003cHR\u003e\u003cCENTER\u003eCopyright 2001 Commissioner.COM Inc and SportsLine.com Inc.\u003cBR\u003eYour site can be reached from \u003cA HREF=http://fantasy.sportsline.com\u003ehttp://fantasy.sportsline.com\u003c/A\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003eFB10SP\u003cBR\u003e\u003c/TD\u003e\u003c/TR\u003e\u003c/TABLE\u003e\u003c/TD\u003e\u003c/TR\u003e\u003c/TABLE\u003e",
  "Attention Fantasy Fans!  Subscribe to \u003ca href=\"http": "//www.sportsline.com/links/6/1/224/sffer1127sn.cgi\"\u003eThe Sporting News\u003c/a\u003e now and get 4 FREE issues! Hurry!\u003cBR\u003e",
  "Content-Transfer-Encoding": "7bit",
  "Content-Type": "text/plain; charset=ANSI_X3.4-1968",
  "Date": "Thu, 20 Dec 2001 09:52:06 -0800 (PST)",
  "Dillon's dislocated finger has improved, and he should be fine for this week. He is listed as probable for Sunday's game against Baltimore. Don't reserve him based on this injury, and only consider benching him based on the Ravens' strong rush defense.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football291.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=782\u0026key=1025\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eScott Mitchell\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB CIN - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/18/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eMitchell could get the start Sunday against Baltimore due to Jon Kitna's strained ligament in the middle finger of his throwing hand. Whether Mitchell or Kitna gets the call, we don't expect either QB to be worth starting in the most important weeks of the Fantasy season.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football291.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=782\u0026key=133415\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eAkili Smith\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e",
  "Don't expect to see Grbac benched this year, or anytime soon, Brian Billick told the \u003ci\u003eBaltimore Sun\u003c/i\u003e. \"He's my quarterback now, he's going to be my quarterback next year, hopefully the year after that and the year after that,\" Billick said. \"The only thing that would change that is if he chooses to retire or God forbid, he'd get a career-ending injury.\" \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football291.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=782\u0026key=1004\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eChris Chandler\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB ATL - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eChandler won't have too look over his shoulder this week. The \u003ci\u003eAtlanta Journal-Constitution\u003c/i\u003e says Michael Vick will not see action unless Chandler is injured. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football291.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=782\u0026key=133322\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eMarTay Jenkins\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e",
  "From": "noreply@ccomad3.uu.commissioner.com",
  "Griese should be able to return from a concussion after the bye week. Jarious Jackson will be Denver's No. 2 QB. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football291.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=782\u0026key=12484\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eJoe Jurevicius\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR NYG - C-Dawg's Boyz \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/19/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eJurevicius (hamstring) is expected to return to action on Sunday. He may be able to catch a deep ball or two against the erratic Seattle secondary. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football291.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=782\u0026key=235216\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTravis Henry\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB BUF - C-Dawg's Boyz \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/19/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eHenry will miss Sunday's game with a sprained right knee. Shawn Bryson will start in his place. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",
  "Holmes is likely to skip practice Wednesday and possibly Thursday due to a sore groin muscle. He is no worse than questionable for Sunday's game against San Diego at this point, but keep an eye on his status before you consider using him this week.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football291.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=782\u0026key=1186\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eBert Emanuel\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR DET - Blue Balls \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/18/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eEmanuel (knee) could be back in the starting lineup this week against Pittsburgh. He will be re-evaluated this week to determine his true status for the game. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football291.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=pro-player-updates\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=782\u0026start=40\u0026\"\u003eMore Updates\u003c/A\u003e\u003cTABLE WIDTH=100% BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=1 CELLSPACING=0 BGCOLOR=\"#000099\"\u003e\u003cTR\u003e\u003cTD ALIGN=left\u003e",
  "Message-ID": "\u003c19164857.1075855439840.JavaMail.evans@thyme\u003e",
  "Mime-Version": "1.0",
  "Subject": "Commissioner.COM E-Reports for Get Bad with Yourself 12/20/01",
  "The Pittsburgh Steelers may be without Bettis for at least one more week. Two days after coach Bill Cowher said Bettis was likely to play Sunday against Detroit, the running back was listed Tuesday as doubtful with a groin injury. \"But this is not a Fred Taylor injury. He (Bettis) will come back and play this year. But we've got to be very careful making sure he's playing in the right games.\" Keep Bettis on your bench this week. His health status makes him too risky a player. Chris Fuamatu-Ma'afala will likely start for Bettis.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football291.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=782\u0026key=12436\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eSkip Hicks\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB TEN - Grid Iron Goons \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/18/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eTitans Head Coach Jeff Fisher said Monday that he plans to give Hicks more work over the final three games of the season, according to the \u003cI\u003eNashville Tennessean\u003c/I\u003e",

{
  "Americas": "IBIT increased 31% to $701 million.  Natural gas volumes increased 6% to 26.7 Tbtu/d, and power volumes increased 77% to 290 million megawatt hours (MWh).",
  "Broadband Services": "IBIT losses were $(80) million in the current quarter compared to a $(20) million loss last year.  This quarter's results include significantly lower investment-related income and lower operating costs.",
  "Content-Transfer-Encoding": "7bit",
  "Content-Type": "text/plain; charset=ANSI_X3.4-1968",
  "Corporate and other": "This segment includes the unallocated expenses associated with general corporate functions. This segment reported an IBIT loss of $(59) million compared to $(106) million a year ago.",
  "Date": "Tue, 16 Oct 2001 07:25:36 -0700 (PDT)",
  "Europe and Other Commodity Markets": "IBIT remained unchanged at $53 million as compared to last year.  While physical gas and power volumes increased, low volatility in these markets caused profitability to remain flat.",
  "Following are the highlights of our businesses": "",
  "From": "no.address@enron.com",
  "Global Assets": "This segment includes Elektro, Dabhol, TGS, Azurix and Enron Wind.  Third quarter IBIT remained unchanged at $19 million compared to last year.",
  "In addition, this quarter we announced one-time charges of $1.01 billion.  Over the past few quarters, we have conducted a thorough  review of our businesses and have decided to take certain charges to clear away issues that have clouded the performance and earnings potential  of our core businesses.  These charges include": "",
  "Message-ID": "\u003c12944379.1075858997589.JavaMail.evans@thyme\u003e",
  "Mime-Version": "1.0",
  "Natural Gas Pipelines": "IBIT increased slightly to $85 million in the third quarter.",
  "Portland General": "We reported an IBIT loss of $(17) million this quarter compared to IBIT of $74 million a year ago.  This loss is due to power contracts PGE entered into at prices that were significantly higher than actual settled prices during the third quarter.  Last week, we  announced an agreement to sell PGE to Northwest Natural.  This transaction is expected to close next year.",
  "Retail Services": "Enron Energy Services reported IBIT of $71 million, compared to $27 million a year ago.  So far this year, EES has completed more than 50 transactions with large customers and more than 95,000 deals with small business customers.",
  "Subject": "Third Quarter Earnings Results",
  "Transportation and Distribution": "",
  "Wholesale Services": "Total income before interest, minority interests and taxes (IBIT) increased 28% to $754 million in the third quarter.  Total wholesale physical volumes increased 65% to 88.2 trillion British thermal units equivalent per day (Tbtue/d).",
  "With our announcements this quarter we accomplished three things": "1) we showed continued strong earnings and earnings growth in our core businesses, 2) we cleared away those things that were clouding this superb performance in our core businesses, and 3) We expanded our reporting of financial results to increase transparency for our investors. To read the full earnings press release, go to www.enron.com/corp/pressroom/releases.",

  ", QB TEN - Houston Big Ballers \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/23/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eMcNair played Saturday despite suffering from back spasms all week. He played well, throwing a touchdown pass in the second half. Expect him to be a solid No. 1 QB.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football291.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=4676\u0026key=146325\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eJeff Garcia\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB SF - C-Dawg's Boyz \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/23/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eGarcia, whose practice time was limited all week, played in Saturday's game. He admitted afterwards that he has a cracked rib. He played with extra padding, saying it didn't greatly affect his throws. Garcia might not be at full strength in the remaining weeks but he will still be a solid No. 1 Fantasy QB. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",
  ", WR WAS - C-Dawg's Boyz \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eWestbrook has been inconsistent this season as a Fantasy player.   "Holt continues to put up consistent yardage totals, but he's only scored only three touchdowns this season. He'll face a tough New England secondary this weekend, but he's still worth starting on your Fantasy team based on his potential to put up solid numbers. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football215.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=2330\u0026key=1294\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eIsaac Bruce\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR STL - Uran Man \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eBruce hasn't put up the huge Fantasy totals this season, but he's still one of the better wideouts in the league. He'll face CB Ty Law and the formidable New England secondary, but he's still worth starting based on his potential for big numbers. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football215.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=2330\u0026key=1109\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eMarshall Faulk\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB STL - Blue Balls \u003cFONT SIZE=1!",
  "Message-ID": "\u003c14680393.1075862392134.JavaMail.evans@thyme\u003e",
  "Mime-Version": "1.0",
  "REF=\"http": "//football215.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=2330\u0026key=235174\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eChris Weinke\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB CAR - Houston Big Ballers \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eAccording to published reports, Weinke will be the starting quarterback for Sunday's game against San Francisco. However, he's not worth starting on your Fantasy team. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football215.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=2330\u0026key=133263\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eDaunte Culpepper\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB MIN - DRock's Beaatchs \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eCulpepper is one pace for a good Fantasy season despite the lack of consistency in Minnesota's offense this season. He's one of the better quarterbacks in the league from a Fantasy perspective, and should be in your starting lineup on a weekly basis. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",
  "Save $.05 a gallon on the gas that keeps your car's engine clean. \u003ca href=\"http": "//www.sportsline.com/links/6/1/226/sffer1113c.cgi\"\u003eClick here\u003c/a\u003e to apply online.\u003cBR\u003e",
  "Smith will return to the lineup Sunday against Philadelphia after missing two games with a sprained right knee. Cowboys Head Coach Dave Campo said after Friday's practice that Smith would \"be ready to play the majority of the game.\" His return bumps Troy Hambrick to fullback, but we wouldn't recommend you use either back against the stingy Eagles rush defense.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football215.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=2330\u0026key=1184\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eFrank Sanders\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR ARI - Dont Mess \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eSanders (hamstring) was added to the NFL injury report on Friday and is now listed as questionable for Sunday's game against Detroit.  However, if you're completely desperate for a wideout in a larger league this week, Sanders' matchup against a vulnerable Detroit secondary is worth considering as long as he's able to play.  \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA!",
  "Subject": "Commissioner.COM E-Reports for Get Bad with Yourself 11/17/01",
  "To": "tstaab@enron.com",
  "Updated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eHuntley will be the likely starter this weekend against San Francisco, but don't be surprised if he splits carries with Nick Goings. Avoid starting either back in Week 10 if at all possible. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football215.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=2330\u0026key=12431\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eDonald Hayes\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR CAR - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eHayes had only two catches for 11 yards last weekend against St. Louis. He's been unreliable for Fantasy owners this season, so starting him is a real gamble.  \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football215.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=2330\u0026key=1321\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eWesley Walls\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, TE CAR - Team Chick \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eWalls has been !",
  "Want to win your Fantasy League?  Our Fantasy Football Guides are the SOURCE for strategy, player ratings, scouting reports, team reports, projections and more!  A must have for beginners and Fantasy veterans alike.  Special in season price $9.99. \u003ca href=\"http": "//www.sportsline.com/links/6/5/12/sffer1113w.cgi\"\u003eGoing Fast - Click Here!\u003c/a\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",
  "Warren will likely start in place of the injured James Stewart on Sunday against Arizona. He's split carries with Reuben Droughns, and is only worth starting as a last resort in larger Fantasy leagues. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football215.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=pro-player-updates\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=2330\u0026start=30\u0026\"\u003eMore Updates\u003c/A\u003e\u003cTABLE WIDTH=100% BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=1 CELLSPACING=0 BGCOLOR=\"#000099\"\u003e\u003cTR\u003e\u003cTD ALIGN=left\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=arial color=ffffff SIZE=\u003e\u003cB\u003eTeams,\u0026nbsp;Rosters\u0026nbsp;\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/TD\u003e\u003c/TR\u003e\u003c/TABLE\u003e\u003c!-- Pizzahut Presenting Logo Spotlight tag - Do not remove until 12-31-01 --\u003e",

  "document.write('\u003cIMG SRC=\"http": "//ad.doubleclick.net/ad/N1549.sportsline.com/B44933.5;sz=1x1;ord=o;ord='+random+'?\" WIDTH=1 HEIGHT=1 BORDER=0\u003e');",
  "href=\"http": "//www.sportsline.com/links/6/5/3/sffer1113ffr.cgi\"\u003e",
  "hroeder (ankle) is not listed on the NFL injury report, and is expected to start on Sunday against Atlanta. He's a solid play this week against Atlanta, whose secondary is vulnerable to strong passing teams like Green Bay. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football215.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=2330\u0026key=187528\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eReuben Droughns\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB DET - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eDroughns will likely split time with Lamont Warren in Detroit's backfield this weekend in James Stewart's absence. Neither back has much Fantasy value outside of deeper leagues, and starting them is a huge gamble. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football215.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=2330\u0026key=1112\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eLamont Warren\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB DET - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT S!",
  "http": "//football215.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/options-ereports?league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5",
  "ld in check over the last three weeks, but he's still one of the better tight ends in the league. He's had some success against San Francisco in the past, so starting him is advisable. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football215.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=2330\u0026key=1203\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eMuhsin Muhammad\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR CAR - Orange Roughy \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eMuhammad finally had a somewhat productive game, catching six passes for 75 yards against St. Louis. He's had some success in the past against this week's opponent, San Francisco, so starting him is a decent move. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football215.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=2330\u0026key=1028\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eBrett Favre\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB GB - Dont Mess \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e",
  "otball215.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=2330\u0026key=1069\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eSteve McNair\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB TEN - Luccis Losers \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eMcNair's status is still in question for Sunday's game against Cincinnati due to an injured right thumb. He threw the ball during individual drills Friday, and according to published reports, is likely to play despite not being 100 percent. We don't recommend McNair this week as a result.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football215.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=2330\u0026key=1094\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eEmmitt Smith\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB DAL - Team Dick \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e",
  "pdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eFaulk had a huge game against Carolina, proving that he is still the best Fantasy player in the league. He's a must-start every week, and should post solid numbers in Week 10 against New England. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football215.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=2330\u0026key=1366\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eErnie Conwell\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, TE STL - C-Dawg's Boyz \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eConwell has had a few down weeks, so starting him on your Fantasy team is somewhat of a gamble. With the lack of depth at tight end around the league, however, starting Conwell is something many Fantasy owners will have no choice but to do. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football215.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=2330\u0026key=1456\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eRichard Huntley\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB CAR - Orange Roughy \u003cFON!",

It is apparent Anderson is no longer worthy of a starting spot on Fantasy teams, and Gary will continue to see some work at his expense.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",

  "document.write('\u003cIMG SRC=\"http": "//ad.doubleclick.net/ad/N1549.sportsline.com/B44933.5;sz=1x1;ord=o;ord='+random+'?\" WIDTH=1 HEIGHT=1 BORDER=0\u003e');",
  "ge Roughy \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/18/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eJohnson caught 12 passes for 89 yards against the Bears, but he failed to get in the end zone again. Don't depend on Johnson down the stretch unless your team is very thin at wideout.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football209.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=968\u0026key=235247\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eDavid Terrell\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR CHI - Really Rottens \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/18/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eTerrell caught one pass for 15 yards at Tampa Bay. The rookie wideout is not consistent enough to start for most Fantasy teams.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football209.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=968\u0026key=133228\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eMarty Booker\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR CHI - Luccis Losers \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/18/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e",
  "he team's next game.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football209.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=968\u0026key=11\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003e Packers\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, DT GB - Uran Man \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/19/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eSafety LeRoy Butler suffered a fractured left shoulder blade during Sunday's game against Atlanta. He is out indefinitely and could miss the remainder of the season. Chris Akins will likely take over the starting duties in Butler's absence. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football209.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=968\u0026key=1069\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eSteve McNair\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB TEN - Houston Big Ballers \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/19/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eMcNair was able to play with an injury to his right thumb, but the \u003ci\u003eTennessean\u003c/i\u003e",
  "href=\"http": "//www.sportsline.com/links/6/5/3/sffer1113ffr.cgi\"\u003e",
  "http": "//football209.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/options-ereports?league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5",
  "reports please to to the URL below": "",
  "says he will probably miss some practice time this week. He should still be able to play in the team's next game.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football209.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=968\u0026key=12411\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eAz-Zahir Hakim\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR STL - Luccis Losers \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/19/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eHakim left Sunday's game against New England with an ankle injury. X-rays were negative, and Hakim is listed as day to day. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football209.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=968\u0026key=235256\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eReggie Wayne\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR IND - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/19/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eWayne suffered a sprained knee on Sunday. His current status is day to day.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football209.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=9!",
  "ue=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=968\u0026key=12623\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eMichael Pittman\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB ARI - Dont Mess \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/18/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eThe awful Detroit defense limited Pittman to 81 rushing yards on 23 carries. Don't start Pittman in any upcoming weeks unless your team is very thin at RB..\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football209.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=968\u0026key=1331\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eDavid Sloan\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, TE DET - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/18/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eSloan caught two TD passes for a total of three yards at Arizona. If you are desperate for help at TE, consider Sloan, who always gets regular looks from Charlie Batch.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football209.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=968\u0026key=1112\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eLamont Warren\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB DET - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated !",
  "ver, the Cowboys will start Ryan Leaf for a few more weeks before Carter gets his starting job back. The team wants to evaluate Leaf in a few games this season to determine if he'll have any trade value in the offseason. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football209.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=968\u0026key=235220\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eJames Jackson\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB CLE - Uran Man \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/19/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eJackson told the \u003ci\u003eCleveland Plain-Dealer\u003c/i\u003e it was a coach's decision not to use him against the Ravens. Jackson had been suffering from an ankle injury, but reports prior to gametime had indicated he might have been able to play. With the sudden emergence of Benjamin Gay, Jackson's Fantasy value might drop greatly.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football209.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=968\u0026key=12506\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eRyan Leaf\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e"
}

  "George played in Saturday's game despite suffering from an ankle injury. He left in the third quarter because of a neck injury but returned to the game.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football291.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=3582\u0026key=1612\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eOronde Gadsden\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR MIA - Team Dick \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/23/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eGadsden did not play in Saturday's game against the Patriots because of a hamstring injury. Chris Chambers started in his absence.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football291.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=3582\u0026key=12207\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eFred Beasley\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB SF - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/23/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eBeasley broke his right hand. He will probably be sidelined for the rest of the regular season. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",
  "Message-ID": "\u003c14080007.1075855439516.JavaMail.evans@thyme\u003e",
  "Mime-Version": "1.0",
  "Moss started off slow this season but has once again been one of the best wideouts. Don't hesitate to start him during your playoff run.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football291.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=3582\u0026key=235122\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eMarvin Minnis\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR KC - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eMinnis hasn't done much to help Fantasy owners this year. Don't use him during the remaining weeks of the NFL season. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football291.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=3582\u0026key=1310\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eMichael Westbrook\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR WAS - C-Dawg's Boyz \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eWestbrook has been inconsistent this season as a Fantasy player. He will be a good No. 2 at best during your playoffs.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",
  "Staley started to play well late in the season. Be sure to keep him into your starting lineup. He will be an adequate back for the playoffs.  \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football291.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=3582\u0026key=133240\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eShawn Bryson\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB BUF - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eBryson will start in place of the injured Travis Henry this week. Consider him as a No. 2 RB if you need help at that spot. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football291.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=pro-player-updates\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=3582\u0026start=30\u0026\"\u003eMore Updates\u003c/A\u003e\u003cTABLE WIDTH=100% BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=1 CELLSPACING=0 BGCOLOR=\"#000099\"\u003e\u003cTR\u003e\u003cTD ALIGN=left\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=arial color=ffffff SIZE=\u003e\u003cB\u003eSchedule,\u0026nbsp;Breakdown\u0026nbsp;\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/TD\u003e\u003c/TR\u003e\u003c/TABLE\u003e",
  "Subject": "Commissioner.COM E-Reports for Get Bad with Yourself 12/23/01",
  "To": "tstaab@enron.com",
  "Toomer is having a bit of a down year, but his potential to post solid Fantasy numbers makes him worth considering. He should be a solid No. 2 wideout during your playoffs.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football291.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=3582\u0026key=1231\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eMarvin Harrison\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR IND - C-Dawg's Boyz \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eHarrison will be an important Fantasy player during the final weeks of the NFL season. He will have some good outings, even though the Colts are not in the playoff race. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football291.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=3582\u0026key=1757\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eDuce Staley\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB PHI - Luccis Losers \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e",
  "Updated 12/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eGonzalez hasn't played as well as expected this year. Still, he is too talented to bench during the Fantasy playoffs. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football291.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=3582\u0026key=1028\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eBrett Favre\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB GB - Dont Mess \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eFavre has been one of the best QBs this season. Count on him to help lead your team to Fantasy glory.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football291.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=3582\u0026key=1599\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTrent Green\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB KC - Blue Balls \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eGreen has been an inconsistent Fantasy QB this year. He is a risky start during the rest of the season. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",
  "Updated 12/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eWarner should guide many Fantasy teams to success during the playoffs. Expect fine numbers from him the rest of the way.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football291.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=3582\u0026key=1034\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eRich Gannon\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB OAK - Team Chick \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eGannon has been a top-flight Fantasy QB this year. He will be a key player on many title teams, and should never be benched. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football291.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=3582\u0026key=12576\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eRandy Moss\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR MIN - Team Chick \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e",

  "From": "noreply@ccomad3.uu.commissioner.com",
  "Galloway has been a disappointment for Fantasy owners this season. Unless you're in a deeper league, starting Galloway during your playoffs isn't recommended.  \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football291.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=4921\u0026key=1253\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTroy Brown\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR NE - Houston Big Ballers \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eBrown has been an inconsistent Fantasy receiver this year. He may not be a reliable option during the Fantasy playoffs. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football291.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=4921\u0026key=1171\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eWarrick Dunn\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB TB - President Taft \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eDunn has been inconsistent this season. He will be a No. 2 back at best during your playoffs. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",
  "Message-ID": "\u003c16825658.1075855439551.JavaMail.evans@thyme\u003e",
  "Mime-Version": "1.0",
  "Subject": "Commissioner.COM E-Reports for Get Bad with Yourself 12/22/01",
  "Thrash was not very consistent during the regular season and may not catch a lot of TD passes in the final games of the NFL regular season. He will be a No. 2 wideout at best during the Fantasy playoffs. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football291.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=4921\u0026key=1790\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eDavid Patten\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR NE - Grid Iron Goons \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003ePatten's numbers have dropped off in recent weeks. Don't use him unless your team is very thin at wide receiver. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football291.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=4921\u0026key=1286\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eJoey Galloway\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR DAL - Team Chick \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e",
  "To": "tstaab@enron.com",
  "Westbrook has been inconsistent this season as a Fantasy player. He will be a good No. 2 at best during your playoffs.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football291.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=4921\u0026key=235213\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eRod Gardner\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR WAS - Houston Big Ballers \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eGardner has been very inconsistent this season. Unless you play in a deeper league, starting Gardner isn't advisable.  \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football291.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=4921\u0026key=1471\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTony Richardson\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB KC - Team Chick \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 12/21/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eRichardson hasn't been a consistent scoring threat this year. Don't use him during the Fantasy playoffs. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",

  "During this busy holiday season, AA.com is the place to find helpful travel information. For more information on traveling during the holidays, visit http": "//www.aa.com.",

  "k?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=568\u0026key=1062\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTony Banks\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB WAS - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eBarring any setbacks, Banks will start Sunday's game against Philadelphia. Banks, who suffered a concussion last weekend vs. Denver, hasn't been feeling any after effects of the injury and should be under center for the 'Skins. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football209.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=568\u0026key=12405\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eJacquez Green\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR TB - DRock's Beaatchs \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eGreen (abdomen) is expected to return to practice on Wednesday at full strength. He's been inconsistent this season, and is best used when the matchup is favorable. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e",
  "random=568\u0026key=1360\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eMark Bruener\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, TE PIT - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eBruener will miss the rest of the season after undergoing shoulder injury. His loss may adversely affect Jerome Bettis' statistics, because Bruener is widely regarded as the best run-blocking tight end in football.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football209.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=568\u0026key=1140\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eTyrone Wheatley\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB OAK - Uran Man \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eWheatley told the \u003ci\u003eContra-Costa Times\u003c/i\u003e he is no longer being bothered by a knee injury. He expects to play on Sunday.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football209.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=568\u0026key=187582\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eErron Kinney\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, TE TEN - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/20/01\u003c/FO!",
  "reports please to to the URL below": "",
  "says there is no indication that Grbac will be replaced as the team's starting QB. Still, he is not performing well enough to start for most Fantasy teams.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football209.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=568\u0026key=133276\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eDonald Driver\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR GB - Free Agent \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eDriver is still dealing with a thigh injury, and is expected to miss Thursday's game against Detroit. The reserve wideout has no real value as a Fantasy player at this point. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football209.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=568\u0026key=3\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003e Ravens\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, DT BAL - Luccis Losers \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eDefensive end Michael McCrary will miss the rest of the season after undergoing knee surgery. His loss will cer!",
  "t he is a key blocker for Duce Staley. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football209.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=568\u0026key=19\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003e Giants\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, DT NYG - Team Dick \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eAccording to the \u003cI\u003eNew York Post\u003c/I\u003e, cornerback Jason Sehorn's surgically-repaired right knee began giving him problems again this past weekend. In fact, the team was unsure that he'd be able to cover either Randy Moss or Cris Carter on Monday night, but he played anyway. If he continues to play on a bad wheel, you should consider starting any receivers opposing Sehorn the rest of the season. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football209.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=98084.5\u0026random=568\u0026key=1035\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eElvis Grbac\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB BAL - Blue Balls \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/20/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eThe \u003ci\u003eBalt!"
}
